493
00:29:08.456 --> 00:29:09.296
Are there any other questions?

494
00:29:11.556 --> 00:29:12.896
Okay. Thank you so much, Tore.

495
00:29:23.036 --> 00:29:24.876
So thank you so much for coming this morning.

496
00:29:25.136 --> 00:29:28.756
It's great to see so many new faces in the cachexia

497
00:29:28.796 --> 00:29:29.816
interest community.

498
00:29:30.836 --> 00:29:34.476
The work I'm going to talk about today is primarily funded by a program project

499
00:29:34.536 --> 00:29:38.046
grant by the National Cancer Institute on the macroenvironment of

500
00:29:38.096 --> 00:29:41.316
pancreatic cancer. The program director is Dennis Guttridge.

501
00:29:41.516 --> 00:29:45.116
The other PI is Mike Ostrowski, and Lenny Coneyars and I lead the

502
00:29:45.156 --> 00:29:47.896
projects at Oregon Health &amp; Science

503
00:29:47.976 --> 00:29:51.876
University with some wonderful postdocs, Ashok Narasimhan, who's

504
00:29:51.936 --> 00:29:54.496
actually in British Columbia, Brittany Counts,

505
00:29:55.356 --> 00:29:57.276
students Sephora Zhan and

506
00:29:58.516 --> 00:29:58.996
Sarah Ota,

507
00:30:00.276 --> 00:30:04.076
in collaboration with Hyun Ro at Indiana University, Shaokai Chi

508
00:30:04.176 --> 00:30:07.666
Zhang, and Tingbo Guo, who have done a lot of computational

509
00:30:07.936 --> 00:30:10.256
interrogation and discovery for us.

510
00:30:11.776 --> 00:30:15.744
So the current-The paradigm of cachexia, as you've heard, is that there is this

511
00:30:15.864 --> 00:30:19.764
wasting syndrome that results from the tumor, and it's really signals

512
00:30:19.804 --> 00:30:23.604
from the tumor that are signaling on the peripheral tissues to

513
00:30:23.704 --> 00:30:27.604
activate this wasting, and that's partly through anorexia, and that's certainly a

514
00:30:27.644 --> 00:30:28.414
component of it,

515
00:30:29.264 --> 00:30:31.764
but also through active catabolism.

516
00:30:31.784 --> 00:30:35.424
And the mechanisms that have been most intensively studied are systemic

517
00:30:35.464 --> 00:30:38.684
inflammation, and this is both cellular inflammation, activation of

518
00:30:38.744 --> 00:30:42.274
macrophages, and also the expression of various

519
00:30:42.304 --> 00:30:45.924
inflammatory cytokines leading to altered metabolism

520
00:30:46.004 --> 00:30:48.424
in all of the tissues that have been examined to date.

521
00:30:49.234 --> 00:30:53.004
And as I said, this happens in part through effects on the brain, inflammatory

522
00:30:53.064 --> 00:30:56.964
cytokines, reducing appetite, altering tumor metabolism

523
00:30:57.044 --> 00:31:00.924
and liver metabolism. And in fat and muscle, which we'll be looking at today,

524
00:31:01.004 --> 00:31:04.814
it's really been attributed to lipolysis and

525
00:31:04.824 --> 00:31:08.784
remodeling of adipose tissue, along with muscle wasting induced

526
00:31:08.824 --> 00:31:12.404
by an imbalance between protein synthesis and protein degradation, which is a

527
00:31:12.444 --> 00:31:15.924
combination of autophagy and ubiquitin proteasome pathways.

528
00:31:16.964 --> 00:31:20.114
And most of this information that we know about cachexia, and I would argue almost

529
00:31:20.144 --> 00:31:23.704
virtually all of it, actually comes from animal models, including mouse models.

530
00:31:24.114 --> 00:31:27.544
And so what is really truly known about people is another

531
00:31:27.624 --> 00:31:30.364
story. But like this review from

532
00:31:31.664 --> 00:31:34.364
Tobias Janowitz's group in "Cell,"

533
00:31:35.184 --> 00:31:39.124
that the clinical picture also demonstrates inflammation followed by some degree of

534
00:31:39.164 --> 00:31:42.924
dysmetabolism. The evidence for this, I think, is less than for inflammation, which

535
00:31:42.984 --> 00:31:45.544
leading to wasting, treatment resistance, and death.

536
00:31:46.184 --> 00:31:46.404
So,

537
00:31:48.424 --> 00:31:52.304
there's a lot of question these days about how well our animal models actually

538
00:31:52.344 --> 00:31:56.184
reflect human disease. And indeed, there was recently a paper in "Nature" that

539
00:31:56.224 --> 00:31:59.674
suggested that rodent models are actually not very reflective of what happens in

540
00:31:59.704 --> 00:32:03.124
muscle in patients with pancreatic cancer and colorectal cancer

541
00:32:03.224 --> 00:32:07.014
cachexia. So we decided to test this directly, and we're comparing

542
00:32:07.044 --> 00:32:10.984
transcriptomes from patients with pancreatic cancer versus our mouse model

543
00:32:11.024 --> 00:32:14.764
of orthotopic pancreatic cancer that progresses over

544
00:32:14.824 --> 00:32:15.264
time.

545
00:32:16.704 --> 00:32:17.344
Our patients

546
00:32:18.404 --> 00:32:22.403
had biopsies taken at surgery, so they're all definitionally early-stage

547
00:32:22.544 --> 00:32:26.064
tumors. And they're significantly different from the control patients

548
00:32:26.104 --> 00:32:29.693
for weight loss and weight change, and weight loss grade, and

549
00:32:29.704 --> 00:32:33.284
myofiber cross-sectional area, and not different for sex,

550
00:32:33.324 --> 00:32:36.884
BMI, or actually total skeletal muscle or total

551
00:32:36.924 --> 00:32:37.604
adipose.

552
00:32:38.684 --> 00:32:40.564
And if we compare these patients

553
00:32:41.664 --> 00:32:45.604
to controls, a case-control analysis, we don't see very many differentially

554
00:32:45.624 --> 00:32:49.114
expressed genes. They tend to be sex-specific and not very many are

555
00:32:49.184 --> 00:32:53.003
overlapping. Some of these pathways have been implicated in mouse models.

556
00:32:54.104 --> 00:32:57.784
But it got much more interesting when we took all of these data and did a weighted

557
00:32:57.844 --> 00:33:01.184
gene-centered network analysis accounting for all these different variables.

558
00:33:01.774 --> 00:33:03.964
And what we found is that the networks that are most

559
00:33:05.324 --> 00:33:09.084
strongly, significantly different associate to weight loss

560
00:33:09.144 --> 00:33:12.824
grade at one month. So acute changes in the body, which makes

561
00:33:12.884 --> 00:33:13.464
sense to me.

562
00:33:14.284 --> 00:33:18.234
And when we look at those, and we look at those pathways in those three modules and

563
00:33:18.264 --> 00:33:21.094
the hub genes, it actually looks very much like mouse models.

564
00:33:21.193 --> 00:33:24.664
So everywhere there's an asterisk here is a pathway that was

565
00:33:24.684 --> 00:33:28.394
discovered or defined or interrogated in

566
00:33:28.424 --> 00:33:30.624
mouse models and likely fly models as well.

567
00:33:30.724 --> 00:33:34.224
So there is truly, at this level, a substantial amount of

568
00:33:34.304 --> 00:33:34.784
overlap.

569
00:33:36.004 --> 00:33:38.134
And so this is our mouse model of cancer cachexia.

570
00:33:38.184 --> 00:33:41.524
It's an orthotopic implantation of a very aggressive pancreatic tumor line.

571
00:33:41.544 --> 00:33:44.944
The mice lose weight over time. They lose fat mass.

572
00:33:45.464 --> 00:33:48.404
The individual muscles and fat pads are lost.

573
00:33:48.464 --> 00:33:52.304
If there's inflammation, they get splenomegaly, and we get loss of liver and heart

574
00:33:52.364 --> 00:33:52.764
mass.

575
00:33:53.684 --> 00:33:57.084
And if we look at the transcriptomes over time, it actually is revealing.

576
00:33:57.144 --> 00:33:59.324
It's not just a long slide to

577
00:34:00.224 --> 00:34:03.784
death. There's actually some interesting temporal

578
00:34:03.884 --> 00:34:07.584
changes. And from a molecular perspective, when we

579
00:34:07.644 --> 00:34:11.504
interrogate metabolism pathways and from if you look at actually the

580
00:34:11.524 --> 00:34:14.944
trajectory of weight loss, you see that there's this early acute shock phase

581
00:34:15.464 --> 00:34:19.384
followed actually by a compensatory plateau not only of weight but of gene

582
00:34:19.404 --> 00:34:23.084
expression. And then there's indeed a slide into a

583
00:34:23.124 --> 00:34:27.054
terminal wasting phenotype. I'm not going to talk about the metabolism aspect of

584
00:34:27.104 --> 00:34:30.804
that today, but it made us think, if this is what's happening in

585
00:34:31.364 --> 00:34:33.603
mice, where are we capturing our patients?

586
00:34:34.223 --> 00:34:35.725
We don't think we're capturing them here.

587
00:34:35.774 --> 00:34:38.604
And so comparisons that have been made to date are really looking at end-stage

588
00:34:38.705 --> 00:34:41.265
mouse models and early-stage patients.

589
00:34:41.274 --> 00:34:45.185
So if we actually then look at our cohort and we stratify by one-month

590
00:34:45.245 --> 00:34:48.225
weight change, and we look at gene expression profiles, would we see

591
00:34:48.324 --> 00:34:51.044
something that we wouldn't otherwise detect?

592
00:34:51.404 --> 00:34:55.294
So this is what we did. And in males, we have about 2,000 genes that

593
00:34:55.344 --> 00:34:58.464
correlate with acute weight loss, and in women,

594
00:34:58.524 --> 00:35:02.344
2,500. And there's substantial overlap with our mouse

595
00:35:02.404 --> 00:35:02.744
model.

596
00:35:03.944 --> 00:35:07.684
And indeed, if we look at a heat map here, there's actually quite a lot of overlap

597
00:35:07.744 --> 00:35:11.344
between mice, women, and men with pancreatic cancer.

598
00:35:11.484 --> 00:35:13.784
And the majority of these are negatively correlated.

599
00:35:13.824 --> 00:35:16.084
That is, they increase with body weight loss.

600
00:35:16.704 --> 00:35:20.564
And a fraction of them are positively correlated, genes that decrease with weight

601
00:35:20.644 --> 00:35:24.594
loss. And then, it's these positively correlated genes in mice that

602
00:35:24.624 --> 00:35:27.364
are less reflective of what happens in people.

603
00:35:28.034 --> 00:35:31.804
But it gave us more confidence that we are using a model that's potentially

604
00:35:31.844 --> 00:35:35.504
clinically relevant. And that's important because we have, and

605
00:35:35.584 --> 00:35:39.244
others, have done clinical trials based on things that we have discovered in mice,

606
00:35:39.824 --> 00:35:43.204
very similar to most other cancer research context.

607
00:35:44.224 --> 00:35:48.044
And if we look at some of the pathways that have been most intensively studied in

608
00:35:48.064 --> 00:35:51.784
mouse models, like the ubiquitin proteasome, and we look at these skeletal

609
00:35:51.824 --> 00:35:55.704
muscle-specific ubiquitin ligases, TRIM63 and

610
00:35:55.764 --> 00:35:59.744
FBXO32, we actually see that there is some

611
00:35:59.784 --> 00:36:03.624
degree of correlation to weight loss, not only in mice but

612
00:36:03.704 --> 00:36:07.244
also in patients, and they might be different between sexes.

613
00:36:08.024 --> 00:36:11.534
And if we look at inflammatory pathways, and this is one that's been of particular

614
00:36:11.564 --> 00:36:14.664
interest in our lab for years, the interleukin-6/STAT3

615
00:36:14.724 --> 00:36:18.424
pathway, that we also see strong correlations, not only in our mouse

616
00:36:18.484 --> 00:36:22.424
model but also in our patients. So again, pushing

617
00:36:22.464 --> 00:36:26.424
back on this idea that our rodent models aren't reflective of what's happening

618
00:36:26.504 --> 00:36:30.220
in human disease.So then to ask what's happening

619
00:36:30.840 --> 00:36:34.720
in the muscle microenvironment, we did some single nucleus

620
00:36:34.820 --> 00:36:38.040
RNA seq studies. So this is in our mouse model. It's done at day 12.

621
00:36:38.060 --> 00:36:41.720
The mice don't have overt cachexia yet. It's an early stage.

622
00:36:42.170 --> 00:36:45.080
And we're already seeing some pretty profound differences in the muscle

623
00:36:45.140 --> 00:36:48.960
microenvironment, including an expansion of myonuclei, a reduction

624
00:36:49.060 --> 00:36:52.900
of fibrogenic/adipogenic progenitors, and some changes in immune cells.

625
00:36:53.480 --> 00:36:57.300
But I want to focus on the myonuclei today, and what we see is that there's a

626
00:36:57.640 --> 00:37:00.200
real identity shift in these cells.

627
00:37:00.280 --> 00:37:03.940
So this red block of cells are myosin heavy chain 4, high

628
00:37:04.000 --> 00:37:06.760
MafH cells, and they really turn into

629
00:37:07.680 --> 00:37:11.480
a group of cells that actually have different

630
00:37:11.500 --> 00:37:15.160
expression profiles. And what we see in the pseudo bulk and for the

631
00:37:15.240 --> 00:37:19.160
myonuclei is that we have a loss of myosin heavy chain 4, and then

632
00:37:19.260 --> 00:37:22.100
interestingly, we have a loss of this transcription factor, Maf.

633
00:37:22.500 --> 00:37:26.240
And Eric Olson's group showed that Maf is actually a master

634
00:37:26.320 --> 00:37:28.800
transcription regulator of muscle maturation.

635
00:37:29.260 --> 00:37:33.020
So Maf comes up at about two months in mouse development, when myosin

636
00:37:33.079 --> 00:37:36.820
heavy chain 4 expression is established, and after myosin heavy

637
00:37:36.880 --> 00:37:40.800
chain 2 and 1 have receded. And then if

638
00:37:40.840 --> 00:37:44.560
you delete Maf, you reduce myosin heavy chain 4 expression, and you

639
00:37:44.620 --> 00:37:47.250
have hypotrophic muscles.

640
00:37:48.360 --> 00:37:51.840
In our cachexia model, Maf declines over time,

641
00:37:52.320 --> 00:37:55.920
and you can see the targets of Maf, which are shown here, also

642
00:37:55.980 --> 00:37:58.800
declined, and myosin heavy chains 1 and 2 increase.

643
00:37:59.280 --> 00:37:59.860
There's this

644
00:38:00.840 --> 00:38:04.810
positive correlation of Maf, which is lower in mice that are losing

645
00:38:04.880 --> 00:38:08.820
weight and higher in mice that are gaining weight, and that corresponds

646
00:38:08.860 --> 00:38:12.360
to the reduction. And there's also, sorry, a correlation with Maf

647
00:38:12.420 --> 00:38:15.900
expression. So Maf and myosin heavy chain 4 expression are correlated.

648
00:38:16.760 --> 00:38:20.560
And if we look at RNA scope and we look at Maf expression, fibers that

649
00:38:20.620 --> 00:38:24.300
express Maf are expressing myosin heavy chain 4, that mature

650
00:38:24.340 --> 00:38:27.599
myosin. And fibers that have lost Maf

651
00:38:28.560 --> 00:38:30.440
are expressing myosin heavy chain 2.

652
00:38:30.450 --> 00:38:34.390
And so you can see it's a pretty robust increase in myosin heavy chain 2,

653
00:38:34.420 --> 00:38:37.429
so a pretty robust change in cell identity.

654
00:38:37.600 --> 00:38:40.520
Myosin heavy chain 1 is also upregulated.

655
00:38:42.380 --> 00:38:45.700
So interestingly, this disturbance of muscle identity is actually

656
00:38:45.740 --> 00:38:49.380
heterogeneous, and it's distinct from that inflammatory and

657
00:38:49.420 --> 00:38:53.400
dysmetabolic cachexia gene program that I have been

658
00:38:53.460 --> 00:38:57.440
alluding to. So overall, if you look at all the myonuclei, there's a loss

659
00:38:57.540 --> 00:39:01.340
of this differentiation gene signature and a gain in what we

660
00:39:01.380 --> 00:39:04.850
call the cachexia gene signature, and these are just literally the top 100 genes

661
00:39:04.880 --> 00:39:08.200
that are changed in skeletal muscle in 22 models of

662
00:39:09.240 --> 00:39:13.120
cancer cachexia. And you can see that these programs are not overlapping.

663
00:39:13.180 --> 00:39:15.279
So there's some intersection between these.

664
00:39:15.560 --> 00:39:18.520
And so this is actually an interesting sidelight.

665
00:39:18.800 --> 00:39:21.760
It is not every myonucleus that is

666
00:39:22.920 --> 00:39:26.440
acquiring these cachexia genes or losing the differentiated gene

667
00:39:26.540 --> 00:39:30.480
program, that these seem to be distinct, at least in this early stage

668
00:39:30.540 --> 00:39:34.040
of cachexia, and maybe they're regulated by

669
00:39:34.620 --> 00:39:38.200
different pathways. And if we look at people, we see

670
00:39:38.300 --> 00:39:42.180
something similar. So the analogous myosin heavy chain in humans

671
00:39:42.220 --> 00:39:45.680
is myosin heavy chain 7. That's reduced in patients

672
00:39:45.740 --> 00:39:49.700
with pancreatic cancer. And you can see that there is a separation of gene

673
00:39:49.740 --> 00:39:53.540
expression of the mature myosin and myosin heavy chains 1 and 2.

674
00:39:54.100 --> 00:39:57.640
And the cachexia genes expression is non-overlapping with

675
00:39:57.700 --> 00:39:59.900
those differentiation phenotype.

676
00:40:00.400 --> 00:40:03.900
However, in severe cachexia, you actually see that there's a trade-off between this

677
00:40:03.940 --> 00:40:07.360
differentiation gene score and the cachexia gene score, such that

678
00:40:07.880 --> 00:40:11.120
if there's more cachexia, there's a less differentiated

679
00:40:12.640 --> 00:40:13.480
transcriptome.

680
00:40:14.380 --> 00:40:16.060
So that's true not only in the muscle.

681
00:40:16.120 --> 00:40:18.560
It turns out it is true in the adipose as well.

682
00:40:18.570 --> 00:40:22.420
And we've known as a field that the adipose microenvironment changes quite a

683
00:40:22.440 --> 00:40:26.320
lot in cachexia. You can see that by simple H&amp;E or Masson's

684
00:40:26.360 --> 00:40:29.260
trichrome. The adipocytes get smaller

685
00:40:30.120 --> 00:40:32.740
through lipolysis. There's remodeling of the

686
00:40:33.920 --> 00:40:37.060
microenvironment. There's a greater fibrosis.

687
00:40:37.100 --> 00:40:39.860
There's an influx and activation of immune cells.

688
00:40:40.520 --> 00:40:44.400
And what we actually observed is also we had occult micrometastases in our

689
00:40:44.460 --> 00:40:47.279
adipose fat pads. But removing those from the

690
00:40:47.900 --> 00:40:51.280
calculation, we have a decrease in adipocytes and a decrease in these

691
00:40:51.460 --> 00:40:54.380
mesenchymal stem cells or adipocyte progenitor cells.

692
00:40:55.280 --> 00:40:59.160
And overall, the picture that we get is that there's actually a dedifferentiation

693
00:40:59.200 --> 00:41:03.160
of the adipocytes as well. And so adipocytes are able to revert back

694
00:41:03.220 --> 00:41:07.040
to a fibroblast stem cell-like phenotype in conditions of

695
00:41:07.100 --> 00:41:11.040
wound healing, and we see that happen systemically in our pancreatic

696
00:41:11.120 --> 00:41:15.050
cancer cachexia model. So we have a loss of genes that

697
00:41:15.240 --> 00:41:18.960
designate a mature adipocyte, including the lineage-specific transcription

698
00:41:19.020 --> 00:41:22.680
factor PPAR gamma. And we have a modulation of these differentiated

699
00:41:22.760 --> 00:41:26.700
adipocytes, particularly a gain of this secretory subset

700
00:41:26.740 --> 00:41:29.680
of adipocytes that we only see in cancer.

701
00:41:29.720 --> 00:41:33.480
This is not just local to tumors that are adipose that might have a

702
00:41:33.520 --> 00:41:37.200
micrometastasis like the visceral fat, but we also observe

703
00:41:37.500 --> 00:41:41.480
the same in the subcutaneous fat. So it's happening distant from the tumor as well.

704
00:41:43.300 --> 00:41:45.420
And we actually did lineage tracing experiments.

705
00:41:45.480 --> 00:41:49.420
So these are mice that express GFAP and mCherry only

706
00:41:49.460 --> 00:41:52.400
in adipocytes through use of an adiponectin Cre

707
00:41:52.500 --> 00:41:56.080
promoter. And you can see that these are perilipin positive.

708
00:41:56.160 --> 00:41:59.960
These are the sham controls. And in the mice with pancreatic cancer,

709
00:42:00.080 --> 00:42:02.840
you can see that they actually retain their

710
00:42:03.740 --> 00:42:07.120
GFP markers, but they develop alpha smooth muscle active

711
00:42:07.480 --> 00:42:08.100
expression

712
00:42:09.100 --> 00:42:12.600
and expression of ICAM. So they're taking on

713
00:42:12.620 --> 00:42:15.880
mesenchymal-like markers while retaining

714
00:42:16.600 --> 00:42:20.460
their markedmarkings of having been an

715
00:42:20.480 --> 00:42:24.360
adipocyte. And that's also clear here in the inguinal fat, where the mice are

716
00:42:24.420 --> 00:42:28.400
still expressing mCherry and GFP but have taken on expression

717
00:42:28.520 --> 00:42:30.480
of ICAM and alpha smooth muscle actin.

718
00:42:30.860 --> 00:42:34.660
So adipocytes are dedifferentiating in this inguinal

719
00:42:34.680 --> 00:42:36.480
fat, which is quite distant from the tumor.

720
00:42:36.970 --> 00:42:39.420
And moreover, if we look at dermal fat, we see the same.

721
00:42:39.920 --> 00:42:40.200
So,

722
00:42:41.300 --> 00:42:45.180
pancreatic cancer is inducing this systemic response to tumor

723
00:42:45.720 --> 00:42:49.600
that's reverting the differentiated phenotype in these adipocytes.

724
00:42:50.880 --> 00:42:54.660
And we see some other changes in the adipocyte progenitor cells as well, but

725
00:42:54.720 --> 00:42:58.320
just for simplicity today, we're actually now interrogating

726
00:42:58.340 --> 00:43:01.960
19 people. We're making an atlas of single cell nucleus

727
00:43:02.060 --> 00:43:04.760
RNA-seq atlas in 19 people for adipose muscle

728
00:43:05.680 --> 00:43:09.480
and tumor. And we see the appearance of these adipocyte low phenotype,

729
00:43:09.540 --> 00:43:10.900
myofibroblast high

730
00:43:12.440 --> 00:43:16.040
adipocyte-like cells in patients with pancreatic

731
00:43:16.100 --> 00:43:17.740
cancer cachexia as well.

732
00:43:19.240 --> 00:43:22.100
And finally, if the tumor is

733
00:43:22.260 --> 00:43:26.020
reprogramming the host, it seems like the host

734
00:43:26.140 --> 00:43:27.800
niche is reprogramming the tumor.

735
00:43:28.220 --> 00:43:29.680
And I give you this example that's

736
00:43:30.740 --> 00:43:33.540
actually supported in the literature, that if you co-culture

737
00:43:35.220 --> 00:43:38.840
pancreatic tumor cells with adipocytes, they mutually

738
00:43:38.900 --> 00:43:42.820
dedifferentiate each other. And we know that if we look at the primary tumor

739
00:43:42.840 --> 00:43:46.400
and we compare it to one of these micrometastases, and we look by single

740
00:43:46.440 --> 00:43:50.360
nucleus RNA-seq, that these adipose pancreatic cancer cells

741
00:43:50.380 --> 00:43:52.210
show a much more aggressive phenotype.

742
00:43:53.180 --> 00:43:56.840
And so they are more basal-like. They also express some classical type

743
00:43:56.880 --> 00:44:00.410
markers. They take on expression of these unfavorable

744
00:44:00.500 --> 00:44:04.300
prognostic markers and are losing favorable prognostic markers.

745
00:44:06.640 --> 00:44:10.460
And then if we look at the top six of these prognostic markers, you can

746
00:44:10.480 --> 00:44:14.100
see they're actually pretty dramatically increased in these

747
00:44:14.140 --> 00:44:16.820
adipocyte resident pancreatic cancer cells.

748
00:44:17.340 --> 00:44:20.620
And each of these is associated with a much worse prognosis

749
00:44:21.500 --> 00:44:25.160
when their expression is higher in people's primary

750
00:44:25.240 --> 00:44:25.780
tumors.

751
00:44:26.820 --> 00:44:30.580
So it makes us think that maybe we need to rethink

752
00:44:31.320 --> 00:44:33.580
this cachexia paradigm,

753
00:44:34.880 --> 00:44:38.680
that in addition to this condition of inflammation, where we

754
00:44:38.720 --> 00:44:42.700
see both immune cell infiltrate into the peripheral tissues, and this is very

755
00:44:42.720 --> 00:44:46.400
well documented in muscle in particular, and

756
00:44:46.600 --> 00:44:50.520
activation of these intrinsic inflammation pathways and the ones that we've studied

757
00:44:50.640 --> 00:44:53.649
most have been STAT3 and NF-kappa B, and others have studied

758
00:44:54.840 --> 00:44:58.040
MyD88 pathways. In addition to that tissue level

759
00:44:58.100 --> 00:44:58.890
inflammation,

760
00:44:59.760 --> 00:45:02.980
and the dysmetabolism, the suppression of protein synthesis,

761
00:45:03.520 --> 00:45:07.510
suppression of fatty acid synthesis, increased protein degradation,

762
00:45:08.060 --> 00:45:10.820
and increased lipolysis, and what we haven't talked about today

763
00:45:12.100 --> 00:45:15.900
is this inhibition of metabolism writ large in

764
00:45:15.940 --> 00:45:18.540
terms of reduction in oxidative phosphorylation.

765
00:45:19.100 --> 00:45:23.040
There's also this background program of cell identity regression

766
00:45:23.460 --> 00:45:27.040
that's induced by the tumor on the peripheral cells.

767
00:45:27.560 --> 00:45:30.900
This leads to a loss or is manifested as a loss of

768
00:45:30.940 --> 00:45:32.920
lineage-specific transcription factors.

769
00:45:33.429 --> 00:45:35.900
And then you get these trajectories of dedifferentiation.

770
00:45:35.970 --> 00:45:39.560
And so not only do you get atrophic muscle, you get identity

771
00:45:39.580 --> 00:45:43.520
regressed muscle. Not only do you get these small adipocytes that

772
00:45:43.540 --> 00:45:46.440
are losing their lipid droplets, they're actually reverting to a much more

773
00:45:46.580 --> 00:45:50.480
stem-like state. And in addition, it's altogether possible that

774
00:45:50.560 --> 00:45:54.520
if that's happening in the adipose to the tumor, if the tumor is

775
00:45:54.540 --> 00:45:58.080
becoming more aggressive because of its contact with or feeding

776
00:45:58.160 --> 00:46:01.940
on the adipocytes, that that could be happening in the primary

777
00:46:01.980 --> 00:46:04.900
tumor in a host that's wasting. So it

778
00:46:05.200 --> 00:46:08.760
suggests that maybe that phenotype that we see of

779
00:46:08.820 --> 00:46:12.620
patients with cachexia who are resistant to chemotherapy, who have

780
00:46:12.660 --> 00:46:16.410
poor surgical outcomes, who are completely resistant to immunotherapy,

781
00:46:16.900 --> 00:46:20.869
that that host biology, the cachexia itself, could serve as not just

782
00:46:20.869 --> 00:46:24.840
a biomarker of treatment resistance, but as potentially a mechanism of

783
00:46:24.880 --> 00:46:28.840
treatment resistance. And I say the evidence for this is that if we can spare

784
00:46:28.850 --> 00:46:31.360
the muscle, we can actually reduce tumor growth.

785
00:46:31.400 --> 00:46:35.300
And we have evidence from that from the field in at least two genetic

786
00:46:35.339 --> 00:46:39.219
models and one from our own, and evidence that

787
00:46:39.300 --> 00:46:41.480
Victoria presented today in mice.

788
00:46:42.360 --> 00:46:44.980
So I'll leave you with that last thought that

789
00:46:45.860 --> 00:46:49.800
I hope you've taken away from this, that our mouse models are reasonable models

790
00:46:50.000 --> 00:46:53.620
of what's happening in patients, and that we should expand our thinking about

